# Next.js Best Practices

## Context

- Applies to all TypeScript and TSX files in the project
- Ensures consistent Next.js App Router implementation
- Maintains performance and best practices across the codebase

## Critical Rules

- Use App Router for better performance and simplified routing
- Implement proper error boundaries with error.tsx files
- Utilize dynamic routing and API routes for data management
- Optimize images using Next.js Image component
- Leverage Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR) when appropriate
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed
- Implement proper loading states with loading.tsx files
- Follow Next.js 15.4.6 conventions and patterns

